{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T01:50:19.951Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777168219951_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-023@20260425T183959Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/metrics.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py`\n- `tests/test_render_metrics.py`\n- `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly adds the `sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` metrics to the render gate. \n- `sampler_event_count_per_piece` extracts event counts from score mappings using multiple common keys/aliases.\n- `sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` accurately computes the ratio across a rolling window of the last 50 pieces, handling cases with zero counts or missing history by returning `inf` or `nan` respectively.\n- The `PASS_BANDS` in `metrics.py` now includes the healthy band (1.5 to 3.0) for the library:self ratio.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria are fully met:\n- Integrated with `metrics.py` (CCH-014).\n- Metrics are surfaced in operator diagnostics with healthy-band tagging.\n- Library:self ratio uses the required 50-piece window and 1.5..3.0 band.\n- Tests in `tests/test_render_metrics.py` and `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py` verify both the computation logic and the diagnostic display.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns in the SenseWeave codebase:\n- `metrics.py` uses the existing `PASS_BANDS` and `_within_band` mechanisms.\n- `operator_diagnostics.py` uses the standard status formatting helpers and `OperatorDiagnostics` dataclass.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. Metric extraction and diagnostic formatting operate on local authority files and score mappings without exposing sensitive data.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-documented, and accompanied by comprehensive tests. \nThe mandatory hardening check for `bootstrap_identity` wiring was verified:\n- `bootstrap_identity()` is correctly invoked in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`.\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py` verifies identity persistence across boots, and all tests passed (63/63).\n\n## Issues Found\nNone.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and well-tested. The use of `math.nan` to skip band checks when history is missing is a good design choice that prevents \"failing open\" while avoiding false positives on fresh boots.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-023@20260425t183959z-verify.md"}}
